; ============================================================================
; Microsoft SoftCard CP/M 2.20 (44K) -- BDOS component
; ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
; A body fragment INCLUDEd by CPM_CCP.asm (the two compile as ONE unit so
; CCP<->BDOS references resolve directly). This file is decoded at the BDOS
; RUN addresses and emitted via DISP so the bytes land at their staging
; position inside the $9300 system image.
;
; STAGING vs RUN (the key to reading this file).  The 5888-byte system image
; loads at staging $9300.  The CCP runs in place ($9300/$9400).  The BDOS,
; however, is RELOCATED DOWN $0200 at boot: its bytes sit at staging $9E00 but
; it RUNS at $9C00 (FBASE; entry $9C06, per CPM_BIOS.asm BDOS_ENTRY EQU $9C06
; and the page-zero JMP at $0005).  So for every byte here:  run = staging - $0200.
; Decoding at run addresses is what makes the absolute operands ($9C47 dispatch
; base, $9F43 param cell, the $A9xx variable page) resolve to real labels.
;
; This INCLUDEd body spans staging $9C01-$A9FF = run $9A01-$A7FF, namely:
;   run $9A01-$9BFF  CCP transient-loader TAIL (spillover ahead of the BDOS base;
;                    CCP_TAIL_* labels) -- staging $9C01-$9DFF.
;   run $9C00-$A6xx  the BDOS proper: image header, $0005 entry + dispatch,
;                    console/line-edit, FCB/directory/allocation, disk record I/O,
;                    RWTS install, error reporter + texts.
;   run $A6B2-$A7FF  static file-data scratch + uninitialized variable page ($E5).
; The handlers for BDOS fns 12-40 run at $A8xx-$A9xx (above this staged image);
; the dispatch table therefore lists them as raw $hex (they are not in this file).
;
; -- DISP/ENT: the CPM_CCP.asm INCLUDE point is staging $9C01; DISP $9A01 makes
;    labels resolve at run addresses while bytes still emit at $9C01.  The
;    external-alias EQU block below re-exports the staging-named symbols that
;    CPM_CCP.asm CALLs/JPs across the component boundary, so the CCP keeps
;    resolving them to the same numeric (staging) values it always used.
; ============================================================================

; -- Page-zero / external symbols (canonical CP/M low memory) --
; [DOC CPMREF 3-44] WBOOT_VEC ($0000): JMP to the BIOS warm-boot routine; most
;       transients return to CP/M via JP $0000.
WBOOT_VEC            EQU $0000
; [DOC S&HD 2-18] IOBYTE ($0003): logical-to-physical device map (CONSOLE/READER/
;       PUNCH/LIST, 4 fields x 2 bits). Read/written via BDOS fns 7/8.
IOBYTE               EQU $0003
; [DOC CPMREF 3-47/3-48] DEFAULT_DMA ($0080): default 128-byte DMA buffer; also the
;       command-tail buffer at program load (length at $0080, chars at $0081).
DEFAULT_DMA          EQU $0080
; [DOC CPMREF 3-46] FCB random-record offsets used below: ex=$0C, s2=$0E, rc=$0F,
;       d0..dn=$10, cr=$20, r0=$21, r1=$22, r2=$23 (see FCB layout, sec.6).

